The paper discusses the development of a stochastic neuron using MRAM technology and its use in building restricted Boltzmann machines (RBMs) for deep belief networks (DBNs). This involves circuit-level modeling and simulation of the RBMs using resistive crossbar arrays and differential amplifiers. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.ET (Embedded Systems), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.EM (Electromagnetics), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
